  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Resistance exercise plus vascular occlusion may induce greater improvements in strength and
      muscle mass resistance training alone. The investigators speculate this training strategy
      could be beneficial in patients with rheumatoid arthritis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
